NAME
    alias - manager for aliases
DESCRIPTION
    Aliases are redirects for commands. For example, you may want `clear` to redirect to `cls`. The alias command is for you.
SWITCHES
    alias add <alias> <command>
        Creates a new alias that redirects to <command>.
    alias list
        Lists all aliases. Note that no aliases are pre-installed.
    alias remove <alias>
        Remove an alias. 
    alias clear
        Clears all aliases.
EXAMPLES
    alias add clear cls
        Creates an alias called "clear" that runs "cls".
    alias add hello 'echo hello world'
        Creates an alias called "hello" that runs "echo hello world".

